<plot>Forgetting the Girl (FTG) is a narrative, feature-length film based on award-winning writer Peter Moore Smith's short story of the same title. FTG is a character-driven, psychological drama about people who are desperate to make emotional connections. Set in Hell's Kitchen, NYC, the film focuses on Kevin Wolfe, a socially awkward head-shot photographer and his endlessly futile struggle to find love and happiness. He encounters a constant stream of beautiful women, but emotional fulfillment continually eludes him. In the end Kevin never does 'get the girl', and the story takes a dark turn as we discover the shocking reality of how he 'forgets' each of these failed romances. The story is as charming and alluring as it is dark and disturbing; it's Sex, Lies and Videotape meets American Psycho set in modern day NYC.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?200743</url></doc>
